<subSubSection id="70EA1288704F6D6F9C9CFC59FA8B296B" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="384F4103704F6D6F9C9CFC59FA8B296B" blockId="4.[151,1436,942,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName id="FFF03A80704F6D6F9C9CFC59FE842EB3" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1835" box="[151,335,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hydropsychidae</taxonomicName>
appears to be a relatively well-diversified group in 
<collectingCountry id="40E70193704F6D6F9FA2FC59FBCA2EB3" box="[937,1025,942,968]" name="Algeria" pageId="4" pageNumber="486">Algeria</collectingCountry>
. Genera and species occupy a wide range of habitats from brooks to large rivers (
<bibRefCitation id="5C613CF2704F6D6F9EAEFC25FCEF2E96" author="Illies, J." box="[677,804,978,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref11782" refString="Illies, J. (1953) Die Besiedlung der Fulda (Insbes. das Benthos der Salmoniden-region) nach dem jetzigen Stand der Untersuchung. Berichte Limnologischen Flusstation Freudenthal, 5, 1 - 28. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1953">Illies 1953</bibRefCitation>
). Three genera of this family are present in El Harrach Wadi: 
<taxonomicName id="FFF03A80704F6D6F9CEBFC01FDA3296B" authority="Wallengren 1891" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1891" box="[224,616,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Cheumatopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A849D11704F6D6F9CEBFC01FE54296B" box="[224,415,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="486">Cheumatopsyche</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5C613CF2704F6D6F9DACFC01FDA3296B" author="Wallengren, H. D. J." box="[423,616,1014,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref15801" refString="Wallengren, H. D. J. (1891) Skandinaviens Neuroptera. Andra afdelningen. Svenska Akademien Handlingar, 24, 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="1891">Wallengren 1891</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FFF03A80704F6D6F9E7FFC01FC72296B" authority="Westwood 1839" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1839" box="[628,953,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Diplectrona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A849D11704F6D6F9E7FFC01FD31296B" box="[628,762,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="486">Diplectrona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5C613CF2704F6D6F9F0AFC01FC72296B" author="Westwood, J. O." box="[769,953,1014,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" refId="ref15927" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1839) An Introduction to the Modern Classification of Insects Founded on Natural Habits and Corresponding Organisation of the Different Families. Longman, Orme, Brown, Green, and Longmans, London, xii + 462 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 12455" type="book" year="1839">Westwood 1839</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="FFF03A80704F6D6F9FF8FC01FAF7296B" authority="F. J. Pictet 1834" authorityName="F. J. Pictet" authorityYear="1834" box="[1011,1340,1014,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A849D11704F6D6F9FF8FC01FB4D296B" box="[1011,1158,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="486">Hydropsyche</emphasis>
F.J. 
<bibRefCitation id="5C613CF2704F6D6F98B1FC01FAF7296B" author="Pictet, F. J." box="[1210,1340,1014,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="486" refId="ref14266" refString="Pictet, F. J. (1834) Recherches pour servir a l'histoire et l'anatomie des Phryganides. A. Cherbuliez, Geneva, IV + 240 pp., XX pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8547" type="book" year="1834">Pictet 1834</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
